== Rituals == The shrine's annual festival features the "Chōkura-iro Dance," which was designated a National {{ill|Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft}} in {{ill|2004|ja|平成16th year|qq=draft}}.
== Cultural Properties == === Akita Prefectural Designated Tangible Cultural Properties === * A pair of wooden {{ill|Komainu|ja|狛犬|qq=draft}} (designated April 2, 1970) * A standing wooden statue of {{ill|Kannon Bosatsu|ja|観音菩薩|qq=draft}} (designated January 9, 1971) – A single-piece carving of {{ill|Japanese cedar|ja|杉|qq=draft}}, possibly from the late {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft}}. * Three standing wooden statues of {{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|qq=draft}} (designated January 9, 1971)
== Transportation == * By Rail: {{ill|JR|ja|東日本旅客鉄道|qq=draft}} {{ill|Uetsu Main Line|ja|羽越本線|qq=draft}}, alight at {{ill|Kisakata Station|ja|象潟駅|qq=draft}}, take a Yokoka-bound bus for 15 minutes, and disembark at Naso Falls.
