During the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo period|qq=}}, the shrine was known as "Zaō-dō" and associated with the {{ill|Ryūzan-ji|ja|龍山寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryūzan-ji|qq=}} temple. It formed a {{ill|Miyadera|ja|宮寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyadera|qq=}} system and was a central hub of {{ill|Chōkai Shugendō|ja|鳥海修験|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōkai Shugendō|qq=}}, attracting many devotees.
