== History == According to shrine tradition, the shrine was established by [[:en:En no Gyōja|En no Gyōja]] as a site to enshrine both Sukunabikona and {{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zaō Gongen|qq=}}.<ref name="akitajiten">『秋田大百科事典』秋田魁新報編、1981st year ISBN 4870200074</ref> In [[:en:Saikō|Jōwa 3]] (856), [[:en:Ennin|Ennin]] (Jikaku Daishi) subdued the giant "Tenaga Ashinaga" of [[:en:Mount Chōkai|Mount Chōkai]] and enshrined the deities Chōkai Daigongen and Zaō Gongen. The shrine may have served as a {{ill|Bettō-ji|ja|別当寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bettō-ji|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} for [[:en:Chōkaisan Ōmonoimi Shrine|Chōkaisan Ōmonoimi Shrine]].
During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], the shrine was known as "Zaō-dō" and associated with the [[:en:Longshan Temple|Ryūzan-ji]] temple. It formed a {{ill|Miyadera|ja|宮寺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyadera|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 別当寺|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 別当寺}} system and was a central hub of {{ill|Chōkai Shugendō|ja|鳥海修験|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōkai Shugendō|qq=}}, attracting many devotees.
In [[:en:1869|Meiji 2]] (1869), the shrine was renamed "Chōkai Shrine." By [[:en:1913|Taisho 1]] (1913), it was further renamed "Kinpō Shrine," incorporating the Kumano Shinmei Shrine on its grounds.
== Rituals == The shrine's annual festival features the "Chōkura-iro Dance," which was designated a National {{ill|Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=}} in [[:en:2004|Heisei 16]].
== Cultural Properties == === Akita Prefectural Designated Tangible Cultural Properties === * A pair of wooden [[:en:Komainu|Komainu]] (designated April 2, 1970) * A standing wooden statue of [[:en:Avalokiteśvara|Kannon Bosatsu]] (designated January 9, 1971) – A single-piece carving of {{ill|Japanese cedar|ja|杉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese cedar|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スギ|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スギ}}, possibly from the late [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]]. * Three standing wooden statues of {{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zaō Gongen|qq=}} (designated January 9, 1971)
== Transportation == * By Rail: [[:en:East Japan Railway Company|JR]] [[:en:Uetsu Main Line|Uetsu Main Line]], alight at [[:en:Kisakata Station|Kisakata Station]], take a Yokoka-bound bus for 15 minutes, and disembark at Naso Falls.
